node.text:
No matter the element, no matter the location, Airmen must be prepared to survive, evade, resist and escape any situation. When it comes to ensuring Airmen survival, it’s the SERE Specialists’ mission to train them. 

Head to the link in our bio to learn more about SERE Specialists. @usaf_gosere

node.title: Being a SERE Specialist in the U.S. Air Force

node.text:
To defeat an enemy against humanity, it takes all of us. June 6, 1944, also known as D-Day, was a crucial moment in the second World War. It took strategy, strength, and most of all, selflessness to achieve victory, but none of it could have come without sacrifice. We remember D-Day and the men who gave it their all for a better world tomorrow.

#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting #DDay

node.text:
U.S. Air Force Special Warfare SSgt Brittany and SSgt Wayne train with @ufc Strawweight @carlaesparza1 at the @ufcpi in Las Vegas, NV. All three of them test their physical and mental strengths as they complete the Eyes on the Prize workout. 
 
Head to the link in bio to learn more about the intensive training Special Warfare Airmen go through. @usafspecwarrecruiting

Disclaimer: Video was shot prior to the COVID-19 pandemic. 

#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting #SpecialWarfare #UFC #MilitaryTraining

node.text:
Happy #PresidentsDay from the ones keeping the President on the move! Here are some fun facts about the world’s fanciest, most functional ride: Air Force One. 
 
✈️ Air Force One is not just one plane—it’s a term used for any @usairforce aircraft carrying the President. 
✈️ Because the President may need to travel to the furthest locations at any given time, Air Force One is capable of refueling midair giving it unlimited range.
✈️ Air Force One is a technological marvel! These aircraft are equipped with advanced secure communications equipment, allowing the aircraft to function as a mobile command center in the event of an emergency.
✈️ Can you say spacious? Air Force One has over 4,000 square feet of floor space on three levels, including an extensive suite for the President, a conference room, a medical suite that can function as an operating room, and two food preparation galleys that can feed 100 people at a time.

#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting #AirForceOne

node.text:
How’s this for #MondayMotivation? 

As the first living and the first enlisted Airman to be awarded the Medal of Honor, SSgt Maynard “Snuffy” Smith was not your typical hero. But on May 1, 1943, he proved that true heroes don’t require a resumé, just the opportunity to prove what they’re made of. 
#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting

node.title: U.S. Air Force: The Snuffy Smith Story

When we think about our health, it’s important to remember that our mental well-being deserves the same attention as any other health issue. 

Being separated from friends and family during the COVID-19 pandemic has been difficult and has caused added stress on our mental health. Watch as @usairforce psychologist Capt Salazar provides creative ways to stay socially connected while continuing to practice social distancing.

As the largest and oldest source of officers for the Air Force, AFROTC, is the elective college course that supports students who wish to become officers in the Air Force after graduation. The organization’s mission is to produce leaders for the Air Force and to build better citizens for America. Watch and discover what you can achieve when joining AFROTC. 
#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting

node.text:
The @usairforce Warrior Medics have stepped up to the plate once again in the fight against COVID-19. The Wilford Hall pathology lab is conducting its own testing on samples taken from patients suspected of having the illness. The lab’s main priority is supporting the 37th TRW and Basic Military Training with in-house testing that allows for quicker results, keeping the Air Force pipeline flowing as smoothly as possible in this trying time.
#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting

node.title: Helping make a difference, one test at a time.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by USAF and USSF Recruiting on August 03, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
Military Working Dogs (MWD), they’re (Air)man’s best friend! 

These hard-working hounds know more than just sit and stay, they’re trained for combat, explosive detection, search and rescue, and more. 💪 

Recently, MWD handlers joined forces with the Black Hawk crews for the first time, in an exercise that acclimates K-9s to helicopters in combat conditions. 

Now THAT’S a loyal pup! 🐕💙

node.text:
Follow these steps to have the best #ImmunizationAwarenessMonth ever: 

Step One: Get vaccinated 💉 That’s it. 

Make like the @usairforce and prepare yourself to face all threats, even the invisible kind.

node.text:
They say friendship runs deep, but in the @usairforce it also flies high. 

Capt Louis Bloom, 36th Fighter Squadron F-16 pilot, left, and Maj Chris Ng, 51st Medical Operations Squadron general surgeon, are truly forever friends. In fact, Maj Ng was key to helping Capt Bloom recover after he got into a motorcycle accident. He used his medical expertise to aid his fellow Airman (and friend) in a full and speedy recovery. 

Despite their initial flight delay, they’re in the cockpit together now. #InternationalDayofFriendship #FriendshipDay

node.text:
Alexa, play our ‘Get Hyped’ playlist. 

Load-bearing workouts are extremely important for Special Warfare Airmen. They never know what situation they could end up in or the distance they’ll have to go to save a fellow service member. 

These exercises will put your strength to the test and show you what muscles Special Warfare Airmen use both in training and when the mission calls for it. See how well you can do in this workout challenge.

These Airmen earned their gym selfie. Have you?

The Special Warfare Operator Fitness Test is given during Special Warfare Prep training and is used as a measurement tool for establishing a baseline of fitness performance. 

Since Special Warfare Operators need to be ready for anything, anywhere, it's essential that fitness is always at optimum levels. See how well you can do in this workout challenge.

node.text:
Ensuring the safety of the people, property, and resources on every Air Force base… now that’s a first-class defender. 

Security Forces specialists go through extensive training in law enforcement and combat tactics to protect bases both stateside and overseas. It’s not a job for the faint-hearted, but their dedication and hard-work ensure every base is properly protected. 

Learn more about Security Forces specialists by heading to the link in our bio!

node.text:
There’s strong, and then there’s ✨Special Warfare strong✨

A Special Warfare Airman’s situation could change on a dime. That’s why it’s so crucial for their bodies to be in peak condition and that they have the strength, agility, and endurance to keep the mission on track and make sure it’s a success. 

See how well you can do in this workout challenge.
